INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (231, 1, '2014-05-07 16:02:40', '2014-05-07 16:02:40', '[et_pb_section][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="4_4"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" background_layout="light" text_orientation="left"]\r\n<h2>Fix All Plumbing Taps the Main Sewer Line for New Construction in the Glassell Park Neighborhood of Los Angeles</h2>\r\n<a href="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.jack_.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-246" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.jack_-200x300.jpg" alt="090807.glassell-park.jack" width="200" height="300" /></a>Fix All Plumbing taps a main sewer line to bring sewer service to the property line of a new home construction in a hillside neighborhood four miles north of downtown Los Angeles. Fix All Plumbing owner, John (right), poses with a worker at the trench.\r\n\r\nAfter ascertaining the location of underground pipes, a ten foot trench is dug from the property line to the sewer main. Workers carefully remove earth around a water main as well as a smaller pipe found nearby to prepare for the sewer installation in Los Angeles.\r\n\r\nAfter the trench is finished workers install safety jacks to support the trench walls. Workers remove additional dirt by hand to provide access to the sewer main and a straight run to the property line.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="1_4"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image1" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.trench.jpg" url_new_window="off" animation="off" /][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_4"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image2" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.trench2.jpg" url_new_window="off" animation="off" /][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_4"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image3" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.sewer-tap.jpg" url_new_window="off" animation="off" /][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_4"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image4" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.sewer-tap-concrete.jpg" url_new_window="off" animation="off" /][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="4_4"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" background_layout="light" text_orientation="left"]\r\n\r\nIn this case, the city sewer main is made of PVC pipe. The sewer main is cut and a flange is fitted to the main creating the new sewer tap.\r\n\r\nThe fitting is sealed with epoxy and encased in concrete.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image1" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.jack_1.jpg" url_new_window="off" animation="off" /][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image2" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.sewer-tap-pipe.jpg" url_new_window="off" animation="off" /][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" background_layout="light" text_orientation="left"]\r\n\r\nThe new clay sewer pipe is cut and connected, and its opening covered and reburied. At a later stage of construction, a plumber will again dig to the new pipe at the property line and connect it to the plumbing of the house.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'Sewer Tap', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sewer-tap', '', '', '2014-05-07 21:42:07', '2014-05-07 21:42:07', '', 41, 'http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/?page_id=231', 0, 'page', '', 0) ; 
