INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (235, 1, '2014-05-14 15:28:59', '2014-05-14 15:28:59', '[et_pb_section][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="4_4"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" background_layout="light" text_orientation="left"]</p><h2>Fix All Plumbing Taps the Main Sewer Line for New Construction in the Glassell Park Neighborhood of Los Angeles</h2><p><a href="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.jack_.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-246" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.jack_-200x300.jpg" alt="090807.glassell-park.jack" width="200" height="300" /></a>Fix All Plumbing taps a main sewer line to bring sewer service to the property line of a new home construction in a hillside neighborhood four miles north of downtown Los Angeles. Fix All Plumbing owner, John (right), poses with a worker at the trench.</p><p>After ascertaining the location of underground pipes, a ten foot trench is dug from the property line to the sewer main. Workers carefully remove earth around a water main as well as a smaller pipe found nearby to prepare for the sewer installation in Los Angeles.</p><p>After the trench is finished workers install safety jacks to support the trench walls. Workers remove additional dirt by hand to provide access to the sewer main and a straight run to the property line.</p><p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="1_4"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image1" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.trench.jpg" url_new_window="off" animation="off" /][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_4"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image2" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.trench2.jpg" url_new_window="off" animation="off" /][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_4"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image3" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.sewer-tap.jpg" url_new_window="off" animation="off" /][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_4"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image4" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.sewer-tap-concrete.jpg" url_new_window="off" animation="off" /][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="4_4"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" background_layout="light" text_orientation="left"]</p><p>In this case, the city sewer main is made of PVC pipe. The sewer main is cut and a flange is fitted to the main creating the new sewer tap.</p><p>The fitting is sealed with epoxy and encased in concrete.</p><p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image1" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.jack_1.jpg" url_new_window="off" animation="off" /][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image2" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/090807.glassell-park.sewer-tap-pipe.jpg" url_new_window="off" animation="off" /][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" background_layout="light" text_orientation="left"]</p><p>The new clay sewer pipe is cut and connected, and its opening covered and reburied. At a later stage of construction, a plumber will again dig to the new pipe at the property line and connect it to the plumbing of the house.</p><p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'Sewer Tap', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '231-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-05-14 15:28:59', '2014-05-14 15:28:59', '', 231, 'http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/231-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
