INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (265, 1, '2014-05-08 00:40:04', '2014-05-08 00:40:04', '<h2>Fix All Plumbing will clear basic drains or septic systems and tanks.</h2>\r\n<a href="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/rooter-5-8-100ft-cable.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-266" src="http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/rooter-5-8-100ft-cable-300x300.jpg" alt="rooter-5-8-100ft-cable" width="300" height="300" /></a>Fix All Plumbing uses professional drain clearing products and equipment in order to clear your drainage problems. Our team of bonded service technicians will come to you with all the necessary equipment to get the job done right the first time and all of our services are guaranteed. We will also give you a job quote before we begin the work.\r\n<h3>Clearing a blocked drain/private sewer</h3>\r\nIt is recommended that you initially check with your neighbors to see if anyone else is affected. If the blockage is minor, you may be able to deal with it yourself and save yourself time and money. A set of drain rods, a plunger or liquid drain opener should be sufficient to clear most clogged drains.\r\n\r\nDo not use unsuitable equipment such as lengths of timber because if some breaks off, the problem can become far more difficult and expensive to deal with.\r\n\r\nProtective clothing should be worn by anyone attempting to clear sewers. However, blockages of a more serious nature will require professional help.\r\n\r\nSewers can be blocked for example by miscellaneous items placed in the system or sometimes by tree roots.  They can collapse through subsistence or break down through general wear and tear. In such instances, or where the sewer cannot be cleared with drain rods, you will need to call Fix All Plumbing your Los Angeles rooter service specialist.', 'Blockage Clearing', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'blockage-clearing', '', '', '2014-05-08 00:42:12', '2014-05-08 00:42:12', '', 261, 'http://dev1.ken-shoufer.com/fixall/?page_id=265', 0, 'page', '', 0) ; 
